# ── Build outputs ──
Sunshine/build/
Sunshine/build_mingw/
moonlight-qt/**/release/
moonlight-qt/**/debug/
moonlight-qt/**/Makefile
moonlight-qt/**/Makefile.*
moonlight-qt/config.log
moonlight-qt/.qmake.stash

# ── qmake-generated files (embed machine-absolute paths & version) ──
# Regenerated on every build from app.pro (VERSION, RC_ICONS, etc.). Tracking
# them leaks per-machine workspace paths.
moonlight-qt/app/Moonlight_resource.rc
moonlight-qt/app/qml_qmlcache.qrc

# ── Temp / Release / Deploy ──
temp/
release/
sunshine-deploy/
moonlight-deploy/
sunshine-backup/
temp_*.cmd

# ── Root-level scratch / per-machine cmds only (not the main build wrappers) ──
# build_all.cmd / build_moonlight.cmd / build_sunshine.cmd / build-config.template.cmd
# are generic wrappers (tracked). Only build-config.local.cmd holds per-machine paths.
/build-config.local.cmd

# ── FRUC standalone test tool ──
tools/fruc_test/

# ── Upstream .github dirs in subprojects (non-functional in subdirs) ──
Sunshine/.github/
moonlight-qt/.github/
moonlight-android/.github/

# ── Android build outputs ──
moonlight-android/app/build/
moonlight-android/.gradle/
moonlight-android/build/

# ── Benchmark / test output files ──
scripts/benchmark/*.json
scripts/benchmark/*.csv
scripts/benchmark/*.txt
scripts/benchmark/.ffmpeg/
scripts/benchmark/vimeo_tri_test/
scripts/benchmark/vimeo_tri_test.zip
scripts/benchmark/benchmark_results/
scripts/benchmark/results/

# ── External dependencies (auto-downloaded by build) ──
vcpkg/
Sunshine/node_modules/

# ── Large binary blobs not needed for Windows build ──
Sunshine/third-party/build-deps/third-party/FFmpeg/FFmpeg/
Sunshine/third-party/build-deps/third-party/FFmpeg/SVT-AV1/
Sunshine/third-party/build-deps/third-party/FFmpeg/Vulkan-Loader/
Sunshine/third-party/build-deps/third-party/FFmpeg/x264/
Sunshine/third-party/build-deps/third-party/FFmpeg/x265_git/
Sunshine/third-party/build-deps/third-party/FFmpeg/AMF/Thirdparty/ffmpeg/
moonlight-qt/libs/windows/lib/arm64/
moonlight-qt/libs/mac/

# ── Debug symbols ──
*.pdb

# ── Packages / archives ──
*.zip

# ── Logs ──
*.log

# ── Compiled objects / binaries ──
*.obj
*.exe
*.ilk
*.exp

# ── FRUC test build artifacts ──
tools/fruc_test/*.exe
tools/fruc_test/*.obj
tools/fruc_test/*.dll
tools/fruc_test/output.txt
tools/fruc_test/build_out.txt

# ── Aftermath dump decoder CLI build artifacts ──
# main.cpp / build.cmd are tracked; built exe + GFSDK DLL are not.
tools/aftermath_decode/*.exe
tools/aftermath_decode/*.obj
tools/aftermath_decode/*.dll
tools/aftermath_decode/*.nv-gpudmp
tools/aftermath_decode/*.nv-shaderdbg
tools/aftermath_decode/*.json
tools/aftermath_decode/DIAGNOSIS-*.md

# ── IDE / tool configs ──
.vscode/
.claude/

# ── AI assistant instructions (machine-local) ──
# CLAUDE.md / AGENTS.md / .cursorrules etc. carry per-machine notes
# (SSH aliases, internal IPs, dev-environment layout) that shouldn't
# travel with the public repo.  Keep locally; never commit.
CLAUDE.md
AGENTS.md
.cursorrules

# ── Per-release scratch notes ──
# release-notes.md is generated per-release and uploaded via gh release
# create --notes-file; the canonical record lives on the GitHub release
# page, not in repo history.
release-notes.md

# ── Generated icon raster output ──
# assets/icon/render_icon.mjs writes Discord / one-off PNG outputs here.
# The canonical icon source is assets/icon/viplestream_icon.svg; the .ico
# and Android mipmaps land in their proper locations and ARE tracked.
assets/icon/dist/
# Local sharp install for render_icon.mjs (~20 MB).  Run
# `cd assets/icon && npm install sharp` if you need to regenerate icons.
assets/icon/node_modules/
assets/icon/package-lock.json

# ── Python venv used for fp16 ONNX conversion + DML benchmark ──
# Built ad-hoc by scripts/convert_fruc_fp16.py / fruc_dml_bench.py.
# onnxruntime-directml conflicts with the CPU-only onnxruntime that
# system Python uses for other repo scripts, so we keep DML in its own venv.
.venv-dml/

# ── Python venv for PyTorch CUDA RIFE export ──
# Built by `cd assets/icon`-style ad-hoc setup or directly:
# `python -m venv .venv-rife && .venv-rife/Scripts/pip install
# torch torchvision --index-url https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cu124`.
# Used by scripts/export_rife_fp16.py to load Practical-RIFE flownet
# checkpoints + emit fp16 ONNX.  ~3 GB on disk.
.venv-rife/

# ── NVIDIA Nsight Aftermath SDK ──
# Free SDK from developer.nvidia.com but redistribution restricted by EULA;
# each developer downloads it themselves, drops the unzipped contents under
# moonlight-qt/3rdparty/aftermath_sdk/.  app.pro auto-detects via lib path.
moonlight-qt/3rdparty/aftermath_sdk/

# ── OS files ──
Thumbs.db
Desktop.ini
.DS_Store

# ── Python bytecode ──
__pycache__/
*.pyc
